Package: scmsens
Title: Sensitivity Analysis Tools for Synthetic Control Method
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: c(
    person("Sooahn", "Shin", , "sooahnshin@g.harvard.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-6213-2197")),
    person("Soichiro", "Yamauchi", email = "soichiro@alumni.princeton.edu", role = c("aut")),
    person("Naijia", "Liu", email = "naijialiu@fas.harvard.edu", role = c("aut")))
Description: Provides sensitivity analysis tools for the Synthetic Control Method (SCM) 
    framework to test the robustness of SCM results to potential unobserved donor units, 
    as discussed in Liu, Shin, and Yamauchi (2024). It extends the traditional omitted 
    variable bias framework developed by Cinelli and Hazlett (2020) <doi:10.1111/rssb.12348> 
    for sensitivity analysis.
